  "img": "icons/dice/d10black.svg",
  "description": "<p>When envisioning a district, think of something like SoHo in New York or Akihabara in Tokyo, a part of a city with a distinct theme, feel, or purpose. This is where Iron City deviates the most from Starforged and start leaning towards Cyberpunk; instead of resource-starved settlements I see cities with skyscrapers and complex social structures.</p><p>In a future where humans can travel across space, a century or two (the proposed time humans have been inhabiting the Forge) is enough for humanity to flourish, and in some places, even decline. Just think about our own history and what think about what 1822 looks like compared to 2022.</p>",
